{"title":"Best iPad mini deals this month","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/677718/best-ipad-mini-deals.html","date":1729517041000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>Apple has finally updated the iPad mini! The new iPad mini launched on October 15, 2024 and went on sale on October 18, three years after the previous generation arrived. The new model is ready for Apple Intelligence (coming with <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2377675/ipados-18-superguide-features-release.html\">iPadOS 18</a>), comes in a new selection of colors, and works with the Apple Pencil Pro. Best of all, Apple has upped the storage, so you now get twice as much for your money. This means the new model offers much better value for money, with 128GB for $499/£499 rather than 64GB for the same price.</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Read about the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/678361/ipad-mini-7-specs-design-processor-release.html\">iPad mini with A17 Pro</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>The arrival of a new iPad mini means that Apple stops selling the older model, although you may find it in <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/shop/refurbished/ipad\" target=\"_blank\">Apple’s Refurbished Store (US)</a> or <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/uk/shop/refurbished/ipad\" target=\"_blank\">Apple’s Refurbished Store (UK)</a>. Beyond Apple, we expect resellers to continue to sell the older iPad mini for a while, and you can expect to see some discounts as they clear out their old stock. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to get your hands on that iPad mini (6th-gen) at the best price, you’ve come to the right place. We are tracking the best deals, as well as the retailers that have models in stock right now. Our advice though is that the price of an older iPad mini will need to be really good to compete with the new models that have double the storage for the same price. For example, the 256GB model now costs $599/£599 where it used to cost $649/£649. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s a deal on the 2024 iPad mini you are after you may have to wait for a little while, but we do see smaller discounts on new Apple products, so there are likely to still be savings to be had if you look in the right places. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Read on to find details of the best places to pick up the 2024 iPad mini (A17 Pro) or the 6th-gen iPad at the best price in the U.S. or U.K. </p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>If you’re after a larger display we also have the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/677736/ipad-9th-generation-deals-best-price-for-10-2in-ipad.html\">best deals on the 10th-gen iPad</a> the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/675139/ipad-air-deals.html\">best deals for the iPad Air</a>, and the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/676751/best-ipad-pro-deals.html\">best deals for the iPad Pro</a>. There’s also a complete roundup of the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/672807/crazy-ipad-deals-for-april-2022.html\">best iPad deals</a>. If you aren’t sure which model to buy read our <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/670670/which-ipad-best.html\">iPad Buying Guide</a> and you may also like to read: <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/668916/best-kids-ipad.html\">Best iPad for kids</a>, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/668914/best-ipad-for-students.html\">best iPad for students</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/678457/which-is-the-best-ipad-for-seniors.html\">best iPad for seniors</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n\n\n<h2>Best iPad mini deals</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll find the lowest current prices on the 6th-gen iPad mini in our automated tables below, but here are the best deals we’re seeing right now. Just keep in mind that these models have been discontinued and you can potentially get more for your money by spending a little more to get the brand new model. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>U.S. deals:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Amazon, <a href=